rComments: this prof mumbles all the time in the lectures. You don't even need to attend to class because you won't understand anything.
he was a terrible prof with a heavy accent, he spoke to quick, and has no compassion in his voice. stay away, unless you absolutely need it

The professor is very down to earth and makes you feel welcome and at ease in class. Also provides great review sessions before assessments. Lectures are information-heavy, and taking good notes on what he SAYS rather than just what is on the slides is important for success.
He is honestly the best. His tests are all based on the things you learned, he always gives a proper outline before a test. Would recommend the course <3

There are more group projects than individual work but the workload is not heavy at all. Steven has very interesting lectures and always involved participation. No need to study much for the final in this course. I recommend taking a scholar course if it can fit in your schedule.

Didn't attend lectures because they are useless. Just googled anything I didn't understand from his slides and studied them. I think the worst part of the course was having Alvin as head TA (very unprofessional and under-qualified). However, labs were actually interesting and tutorials were helpful. His tests were easy just study his lecture slides
He cares a lot for students ut doesn't know how to teach in class. I found bio203 super boring but bio314 was easier for me (molecular bio specialist here) and better

Great prof! It was hard to understand his lectures mostly bc it felt he was mumbling all the time. But once u get to know him, amazing person and really cares for his students. Attendance is optional and don't waste time reading the book bc everything is in his slides. Labs are easy depending on your TA.

He's very monotone, which makes it hard to listen to him. but he is very nice and answers questions in class and outside of class. you MUST memorize his lecture slides and make good notes in class if you want an easier time. textbook is pretty important (he tels u where he gets his questions from in the book, which is very nice)
his tests were fair, lectures were a tad boring, but it's probably because it was plants he's very funny amazing prof
Fantastic prof. Very approachable and is willing to go the extra mile to make sure you understand the material. Super friendly during office hours and tests are fair if you do your part and study.

Great prof, shows great mastery of the material and is energetic in lectures. Was in every lab taking feedback from students too. Attend lectures, take notes, forget about the textbooks. Got an A in both.
This year is his 1st yr teaching BIO203, a new course about plant biology
